          <li>$23.1M: This is similar to my estimation model using training compute and hardware price-performance. However, here the cloud compute price is substituted for the (<em>hardware_unit_price / hardware_replacement_time</em>) formula that I used. This $/s value converts FLOP/s into FLOP/$.</li>
          <li>$9.2M: This is similar to the method for (a), but uses the cloud compute pricing of <a href="https://lambdalabs.com/service/gpu-cloud" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">LambdaLabs</a> and substitutes an NVIDIA A100 GPU for the TPU V4.</li>
